next
  Summary: Loot Balance. Online NPCs are continuously trimmed so long-lived stalkers (story NPCs, companions, gulag survivors) never accumulate corpse-sized hoards. Traders are skipped so their stock is untouched. Smart Pacing renamed to Smart Balance (label only, no behavior change).
  Added:
    Added: Loot Balance. Periodic scanner walks online stalkers in small batches and trims each one at most once per game-day. The population that survives is the population that hoards, so hundreds of long-lived stalkers kept driving save bloat, server-object inflation, and steady performance drag under the previous death-time approach. The scanner closes that gap. Per-NPC policy keeps: quest items (engine quest flag plus vanilla [keep_items] whitelist for quest-given uniques whose item class is normal), money, equipped weapon and ammo for that weapon, worn outfit and helmet, vanilla [keep_one] grenades, player-gifted items, player-strapped weapons, up to 2 extra non-equipped weapons / outfits / helmets / artefacts (the loot-to-sell pool, MCM-tunable), and up to 3 of each stackable consumable. The 3rd+ non-equipped weapon, outfit, helmet, or artefact is released, as is ammo for weapons the NPC is not carrying, and 4th+ of any stackable consumable. Traders are skipped at the scheduler level (utils_obj.is_trader): community=trader, clsid script_trader/trader, section name containing "trader", or storage logic with a trade line. Public API at module scope (trim_npc, evaluate_item, build_state, default_policy) lets probes, MCM buttons, and other mods drive trimming externally or compose with the default policy. MCM (General -> Loot Balance) defaults: enable on, NPCs per frame 1, NPCs per cycle 20, per-NPC rescan cooldown 24 game-hours, surplus per category 2. Requires NPC corpse looting enabled. Disable "311- NPC Stop Looting Dead Bodies - DTTheGunslinger" or any equivalent NPC-loot disabler for full benefit.
  Changed:
    Renamed: Smart Pacing is now labelled Smart Balance in MCM, readme, and architecture. Label only, no behavior change. Internal script and config keys (ab_pacing, last_respawn_update, advances, min_minutes) unchanged.

1.0.2
  Summary: Crash fix on xlibs 1.7.0
  Fixed:
    Fixed: Crash in Smart Pacing on xlibs 1.7.0 at ab_recipe.script:141. Adopt renamed xsmart.find_smarts_spawning (was xsmart.find_smarts_with_recipe pre-1.7.0). Requires xlibs 1.7.0+.

1.0.1
  Summary: Crash fix on malformed respawn params, third-party respawn-delay compatibility
  Fixed:
    Fixed: Crash in Smart Pacing budget evaluation when scanning malformed or misconfigured smart terrains whose respawn_params.num condlist has no default branch.
  Compatibility:
    Skip smart terrains whose last_respawn_update is set to a future game-time by another mod. Honors third-party deferred-respawn intent instead of overriding it.

1.0.0
  First release. Advances respawn cooldowns at smart terrains where combat has produced deaths, so active regions recover faster without affecting the rest of the map.
